# Socket.io Real-time Monitoring Events Documentation

**Last Updated**: May 18, 2026  
**Status**: ✅ Fully Implemented  
**Service**: Scraper Management System

---

## Overview

The Scraper Management System uses Socket.io for real-time monitoring of scraper jobs and queue updates. All events are emitted by the `ScraperQueueService` and can be subscribed to by clients through the Socket.io connection.

---

## Connection Setup

### Server-side (index.ts)

Socket.io is initialized in `apps/gateway/src/index.ts`:

```typescript
import { Server } from 'socket.io';
import { setSocketInstance } from './services/socketManager';

// Socket.io setup
const io = new Server(fastify.server, {
  cors: {
    origin: '*',
  },
});

setSocketInstance(io);

io.on('connection', (socket) => {
  // Scraper monitoring handlers
  socket.on('scraper:subscribe', (data) => {
    const { sourceId } = data || {};
    if (sourceId) {
      socket.join(`scraper:${sourceId}`);
    } else {
      socket.join('scraper:all');
    }
  });

  socket.on('scraper:unsubscribe', (data) => {
    const { sourceId } = data || {};
    if (sourceId) {
      socket.leave(`scraper:${sourceId}`);
    } else {
      socket.leave('scraper:all');
    }
  });
});
```

### Client-side Connection

```typescript
import io from 'socket.io-client';

const socket = io('http://localhost:4000');

// Subscribe to all scraper events
socket.emit('scraper:subscribe', {});

// Subscribe to specific source events
socket.emit('scraper:subscribe', { sourceId: 'source-123' });
```

---

## Event Types

### 1. scraper:job:started

**Emitted when**: A scraper job starts execution  
**Source**: `ScraperQueueService.dequeueJob()`  
**Location**: `apps/gateway/src/services/scraperQueueService.ts:145`

**Event Data Structure**:
```typescript
{
  job: {
    id: string;              // Unique job ID (e.g., "job-1234567890-1")
    sourceId: string;        // Scraper source ID
    status: 'RUNNING';       // Job status
    retryCount: number;      // Current retry count
    maxRetries: number;      // Maximum retry attempts
    startedAt: Date;         // Job start timestamp
    createdAt: Date;         // Job creation timestamp
    priority: number;        // Job priority (higher = more important)
  },
  queueStats: {
    total: number;           // Total jobs in queue
    pending: number;         // Pending jobs
    running: number;         // Running jobs
    completed: number;       // Completed jobs
    failed: number;          // Failed jobs
    avgWaitTime: number;     // Average wait time (ms)
    avgProcessTime: number;  // Average process time (ms)
  }
}
```

**Example**:
```typescript
socket.on('scraper:job:started', (data) => {
  console.log(`Job ${data.job.id} started for source ${data.job.sourceId}`);
  console.log(`Queue stats: ${data.queueStats.running} running, ${data.queueStats.pending} pending`);
});
```

---

### 2. scraper:job:progress

**Emitted when**: Job progress is updated during execution  
**Source**: `ScraperQueueService.updateJobProgress()`  
**Location**: `apps/gateway/src/services/scraperQueueService.ts:583`

**Event Data Structure**:
```typescript
{
  jobId: string;           // Job ID
  sourceId: string;        // Scraper source ID
  progress: {
    percentage?: number;   // Progress percentage (0-100)
    message?: string;      // Progress message
    itemsProcessed?: number; // Items processed so far
    totalItems?: number;   // Total items to process
  },
  timestamp: Date;         // Progress update timestamp
}
```

**Example**:
```typescript
socket.on('scraper:job:progress', (data) => {
  console.log(`Job ${data.jobId}: ${data.progress.percentage}% - ${data.progress.message}`);
  console.log(`Processed ${data.progress.itemsProcessed}/${data.progress.totalItems} items`);
});
```

---

### 3. scraper:job:completed

**Emitted when**: A scraper job completes successfully  
**Source**: `ScraperQueueService.completeJob()`  
**Location**: `apps/gateway/src/services/scraperQueueService.ts:201`

**Event Data Structure**:
```typescript
{
  job: {
    id: string;              // Job ID
    sourceId: string;        // Scraper source ID
    status: 'SUCCESS';       // Job status
    retryCount: number;      // Total retry attempts made
    maxRetries: number;      // Maximum retry attempts
    startedAt: Date;         // Job start timestamp
    completedAt: Date;       // Job completion timestamp
    createdAt: Date;         // Job creation timestamp
    priority: number;        // Job priority
    result?: any;            // Job result data
  },
  queueStats: {
    total: number;           // Total jobs in queue
    pending: number;         // Pending jobs
    running: number;         // Running jobs
    completed: number;       // Completed jobs
    failed: number;          // Failed jobs
    avgWaitTime: number;     // Average wait time (ms)
    avgProcessTime: number;  // Average process time (ms)
  }
}
```

**Example**:
```typescript
socket.on('scraper:job:completed', (data) => {
  const duration = data.job.completedAt.getTime() - data.job.startedAt.getTime();
  console.log(`Job ${data.job.id} completed in ${duration}ms`);
  console.log(`Result:`, data.job.result);
});
```

---

### 4. scraper:job:failed

**Emitted when**: A scraper job fails (with or without retry)  
**Source**: `ScraperQueueService.failJob()`  
**Location**: `apps/gateway/src/services/scraperQueueService.ts:268` (retry) and `:295` (permanent failure)

**Event Data Structure**:
```typescript
{
  job: {
    id: string;              // Job ID
    sourceId: string;        // Scraper source ID
    status: 'PENDING' | 'FAILED'; // 'PENDING' if will retry, 'FAILED' if permanent
    retryCount: number;      // Current retry count
    maxRetries: number;      // Maximum retry attempts
    startedAt?: Date;        // Job start timestamp
    completedAt?: Date;      // Job completion timestamp (if permanent failure)
    createdAt: Date;         // Job creation timestamp
    priority: number;        // Job priority
    error?: string;          // Error message
  },
  willRetry: boolean;        // Whether job will be retried
  errorType?: string;        // Error classification type
  retryDelay?: number;       // Delay before retry (ms) - only if willRetry=true
  queueStats: {
    total: number;           // Total jobs in queue
    pending: number;         // Pending jobs
    running: number;         // Running jobs
    completed: number;       // Completed jobs
    failed: number;          // Failed jobs
    avgWaitTime: number;     // Average wait time (ms)
    avgProcessTime: number;  // Average process time (ms)
  }
}
```

**Example**:
```typescript
socket.on('scraper:job:failed', (data) => {
  if (data.willRetry) {
    console.log(`Job ${data.job.id} failed, will retry in ${data.retryDelay}ms`);
    console.log(`Error type: ${data.errorType}`);
  } else {
    console.log(`Job ${data.job.id} failed permanently: ${data.job.error}`);
  }
});
```

