### 5. scraper:queue:updated

**Emitted when**: Queue state changes (job enqueued or queue cleared)  
**Source**: `ScraperQueueService.enqueueJob()` and `ScraperQueueService.clearAll()`  
**Location**: `apps/gateway/src/services/scraperQueueService.ts:87` and `:547`

**Event Data Structure**:
```typescript
{
  action: 'enqueued' | 'cleared'; // Action type
  job?: {                    // Only present when action='enqueued'
    id: string;              // Job ID
    sourceId: string;        // Scraper source ID
    status: 'PENDING';       // Job status
    retryCount: number;      // Current retry count
    maxRetries: number;      // Maximum retry attempts
    createdAt: Date;         // Job creation timestamp
    priority: number;        // Job priority
  },
  queueStats: {
    total: number;           // Total jobs in queue
    pending: number;         // Pending jobs
    running: number;         // Running jobs
    completed: number;       // Completed jobs
    failed: number;          // Failed jobs
    avgWaitTime: number;     // Average wait time (ms)
    avgProcessTime: number;  // Average process time (ms)
  }
}
```

**Example**:
```typescript
socket.on('scraper:queue:updated', (data) => {
  if (data.action === 'enqueued') {
    console.log(`New job ${data.job.id} added to queue`);
  } else if (data.action === 'cleared') {
    console.log('Queue cleared');
  }
  console.log(`Queue size: ${data.queueStats.total}`);
});
```

